This paper discusses software transactional memory systems, which are commonly used in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses programming languages and concurrency issues, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper mentions databases, which could place it in cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses operating systems and correctness criteria, which could place it in cs.OS (Operating Systems). Finally, the paper discusses implementation and performance, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering).
